BR.FONT: Start Zofran tablet, 4 mg, 1 tab(s), orally, every 8 hours, 12, Refills 0

Notes: I have diagnosed Coralina with viral gastroenteritis. Differential diagnosis considered include (but not limited to) viral gastroenteritis, diverticular disease, food intolerance, irritable bowel syndrom, intestinal obstruction, hernia, and ulcerative colitis. More serious diagnosis considered less likely include infectious colitis, Crohn's, and bowel infarction. For treatment I will prescribe Zofran. Over the counter interventions for symptom management include sugar free Gatoraide and Imodium. Return to clinic if not improving within 2-3 days, sooner if worse. Proceed to ED if significantly worse after clinic hours. I recommend that she push fluids, avoiding sports drinks with lots of sugar. I recommended occasionally drinking chicken or beef broth with water in between, Pedialyte, or sugar-free sports drinks. I discussed at length with Coralina the signs and symptoms of orthostasis and to use caution while standing up to avoid potential injury from passing out. If not improving with fluid hydration I recommend proceeding to the ED to consider IV hydration.
